1 packet Crispy Shallots
1 sachet Coriander
6 Mini Flour Tortillas
500 g Pork Mince
1 packet Teriyaki Sauce
1 Pear
1 Carrot
1 packet Garlic Aioli
1 packet Shredded Cabbage Mix
1 packet Garlic Paste
1 drizzle olive oil
tbs brown sugar

• Grate carrot. Thinly slice pear into sticks. Finely chop coriander (see ingredients).

• Heat a large frying pan over high heat with a drizzle of olive oil. Cook pork mince, breaking up with a spoon, until browned, 4-5 minutes (cook in batches if your pan is getting crowded).
• Return all mince to pan, then add garlic paste and cook until fragrant, 1 minute.
• Add teriyaki sauce, the vinegar and brown sugar, then cook, stirring, until the sauce is slightly reduced, 1 minute.
• Remove from heat. Season with pepper.

• Meanwhile, combine shredded cabbage mix, carrot, pear, coriander and a drizzle of vinegar and olive oil in a large bowl.
• Heat mini flour tortillas on a plate in the microwave in 10 second bursts, until warmed through.
Little cooks: Kids can help with combining the slaw!

• Top each tortilla with slaw and teriyaki pork.
• Dollop with garlic aioli and sprinkle over crispy shallots to serve. Enjoy!
Little cooks: Take the lead and help build the tacos!